'''[[Cannabis]] in [[Kazakhstan]]''' is illegal. 

Extensive amounts of cannabis grow wild in the country.<ref name="Board2005">{{cite book|author=International Narcotics Control Board|title=Report of the International Narcotics Control Board 2004: 2005|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=XbBSu-z99bsC&pg=PA68|date=1 April 2005|publisher=United Nations Publications|isbn=978-92-1-148198-3|pages=68–}}</ref> The 2006 ''World Drug Report'' estimated that 400,000 hectares of cannabis grow wild in the [[Chui Valley]].<ref name="Crime2006">{{cite book|author=United Nations Office on Drugs and Crime|title=2006 World Drug Report: Analysis|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=Lk8wDdoxTZsC&pg=PA2096|year=2006|publisher=United Nations Publications|isbn=978-92-1-148214-0|pages=2096–}}</ref>

Per Russia's Ministry of Internal Affairs, 93% of the nation's marijuana comes from Kazakhstan.<ref name="MenonFedorov2016">{{cite book|last1=Menon|first1=Rajan|last2=Fedorov|first2=Yuri E.|last3=Nodia|first3=Ghia|publisher=East West Institute|title=Russia, the Caucasus, and Central Asia|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=bHqTDAAAQBAJ&pg=PA230|date=July 2016|via=Routledge|isbn=978-1-315-50172-7|page=230}}</ref>

